Very usecase specific for my Samsung Series 9 NP900X3C running KDE OpenSuse

Detects three and four finger (or more) gestures on the touchpad via synaptics
shared memory and sends key presses which you then bind to Global Keyboard Shortcuts

Requires:

Option "SHMConfig" "true"
    in X11 xorg.conf

libX11

libXtst

INSTALL:
$ make all
$ make install

For questions or queries contact me at vanderhoornm@gmail.com
